comment:
What a bunch of shit.  This isn't a bombshell.  I'll post from the BBC article that followed Depp losing the case.

'Mr Depp, 57, sued the paper after it claimed he assaulted his ex-wife Amber Heard, which he denies. The Sun said the article was accurate.
Judge Mr Justice Nicol said the Sun had proved what was in the article to be "substantially true"... He found 12 of the 14 alleged incidents of domestic violence had occurred.'

'The trial was heard over 16 days in July at the Royal Courts of Justice in London.'

"Taking all the evidence together, I accept that she was the victim of sustained and multiple assaults by Mr Depp in Australia," said Mr Justice Nicol...."It is a sign of the depth of his rage that he admitted scrawling graffiti in blood from his injured finger and then, when that was insufficient, dipping his badly injured finger in paint and continuing to write messages and other things," the judge said.'

"I accept her evidence of the nature of the assaults he committed against her. They must have been terrifying."

Bryan singer, Bill Cosby, Kevin Spacey, Johnny Depp, Donald Trump...just because you like someone's work or admire their talent, doesn't mean you know them.  Famous people are sometimes shitty people.  They do shitty things and are NOT the people the media sells to you.  This is the nature of the media; protect assets.

A sixteen day trial gave Depp's crack legal team, funded by the weight of numerous studios, his agency and his own measurable wealth, failed to prove his innocence.  Not only this, they PROVED that 12 out of 14 incidents of physical abuse were substantiated by physical evidence.  This strongly suggests that Depp was in fact, guilty.

Before you throw out mindless defence of a man you have never met, never will meet and who will never want to meet you, or caustic abuse at a woman who may or may not be a nice person but was proved by a court of law to be the victim of physical abuse ... consider where your evidence comes from.

Tabloids are NOT your legal team.  Movie stars are fallible.  

The proven abuse of ANYONE is unacceptable...don't champion it?

comment: I truely feel for Johnny and what hes had to endure since starting a relationship with AH. I have experience with a woman like AH. My fathers girlfriend who was 20 years his junior was verbally and emotionally abusive towards him. We never thought it was physical tho. But in 2018 on his 54th birthday, at 8.30 pm after my dad had a great day and was especially happy as he saw and spoke to my brother, who hadnt spoke to him for nearly 10 years as he still had alot of anger about my dad moving to a different country after him and our mum got divorced but they had a great talk and were planning to meet up and try build up a relationship again. She didnt like this and kept making little digs at him about being an absent father, we know this as my other brother and my gran were there at this point but after they left neighbours said they heard arguing but then it all went quiet abt 8.30. She had attacked him with a whisky bottle and she didnt stop attacking him until he was unrecognisable and his body was covers in cuts. She didnt call the ambulance til the next moring but by then he had been dead for hours. His body was so bad they wouldnt let us id him so they had to take our dna to id him. We never got to see his body. She brought friends over and showed them his body hours before calling the ambulance, she also changed clothes, disposed of the bottle in an outside bin. She said she attacked him because he bit her bum. See took a plea deal for culpable homicide, which only happened 20 mins before her murder trial was suppose to start. She was sentenced to 7 years but will be up for parole in Oct 2021. That plea deal and her sentence felt like a slap in the face to me and my family. I really hope Johnny gets justice.
